 "\nMust either use Clear[Subscript] to clear all subscripted variables or ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["K", "1"], "=."}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "bb7ad4a3-bbd3-4fd4-a6b7-6409bd26cf17"],
 " to clear just ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["K", "1"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "42513b69-f1bd-4f95-9039-b242ac77e123"],
 "\n\nIt is OK to use the same symbol for a constant, one  variable, and two \
variables\nIt is also OK to set A[t,r] = A[t], but  not OK to set  A[t]=A, a \
constant\n     Because if later set A=1, then Mathematica displays A[t] as \
1[t] . \n     In general, to be safe from such idiosyncrasies, I use \
different fonts for the symbols: \n          Regular A[t,r], double-strike \
\[DoubleStruckCapitalC][t,r],  script \[ScriptCapitalA][t], Greek \
\[CapitalAlpha][r] or Gothic \[GothicCapitalC][r]\n          I use symbols \
like  k or Greek \[Alpha]  for constants.  \n          So, \
\[ScriptCapitalA][t] = \[Alpha] and later \[Alpha]=1 is OK.\n\nMathematica \
generally uses  K[1] for the integration dummy variable.\n     To make this \
easier to read, I use rulesKr to change, for example, \[CapitalBeta][K[1]] \
dK[1]  to \[CapitalBeta][\[Rho]] d\[Rho]\n     For dummy t, I use rulesKt to \
get, for example, \[ScriptCapitalA][\[Tau]] d\[Tau]\n\nFor double integrals, \
Mathematica generally uses K[2] for the outer dummy variable and K[1] for the \
inner dummy variable.\n     For readability, I make the substitution \
/.rulesKKr\n\nWarning: for readability of integrals, I follow /.rulesKr or \
/.rulesKt with /.rulesDisp,\n     This makes complex expressions with \
functions of \[Rho], \[Sigma], and \[Tau] more readable\n     For example, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
   RowBox[{"-", 
    TemplateBox[{
      RowBox[{
        FractionBox["1", "2"], " ", 
        RowBox[{"(", 
          RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"-", 
              FractionBox["4", "\[Sigma]"]}], "+", 
            FractionBox[
             SuperscriptBox[
             "\[CapitalBeta]", "\[Prime]", MultilineFunction -> None], 
             "\[CapitalBeta]"], "-", 
            FractionBox[
             
             RowBox[{"2", " ", 
               "\"\\!\\(\\*SuperscriptBox[SubscriptBox[\\(\[GothicCapitalD]\\)\
, \\(4\\)], \\(\[DoublePrime]\\)]\\)\""}], 
             SuperscriptBox[
              SubscriptBox["\[GothicCapitalD]", "4"], "\[Prime]", 
              MultilineFunction -> None]], "-", 
            FractionBox[
             RowBox[{"4", " ", "\[CapitalBeta]", " ", 
               RowBox[{"(", 
                 RowBox[{
                   RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{"-", "2"}], " ", 
                    SuperscriptBox["c", "2"]}], "+", 
                   RowBox[{"k", " ", "\[CapitalLambda]", " ", 
                    SubscriptBox["\[GothicCapitalD]", "4"]}]}], ")"}]}], 
             RowBox[{"k", " ", 
               SuperscriptBox[
                SubscriptBox["\[GothicCapitalD]", "4"], "\[Prime]", 
                MultilineFunction -> None]}]], "-", 
            FractionBox[
             SuperscriptBox[
              SubscriptBox["\[GothicCapitalD]", "4"], "\[Prime]", 
              MultilineFunction -> None], 
             SubscriptBox["\[GothicCapitalD]", "4"]]}], ")"}]}], "\[Rho]", 
      "1", "r"},
     "InactiveIntegrate",
     DisplayFunction->(RowBox[{
        SubsuperscriptBox[
         StyleBox["\[Integral]", "Inactive"], #3, #4], 
        RowBox[{#, 
          RowBox[{
            StyleBox["\[DifferentialD]", "Inactive"], #2}]}]}]& ),
     InterpretationFunction->(RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"Inactive", "[", "Integrate", "]"}], "[", 
        RowBox[{#, ",", 
          RowBox[{"{", 
            RowBox[{#2, ",", #3, ",", #4}], "}"}]}], "]"}]& )]}]]], "Print",
